{
  "texts": [
    "For concreteness we will restrict ourselves to κ = 0 since Hermitian analyticity has been well-established in this case.",
    "To match the notation of [24] we define σ- h (η, k) ≡ -iσ h (η, k) and σ + h (η, k) ≡ +iσ * h (η, k).",
    "We then have 19 σ - h (η, k) = -i H √ π 2 (-η)3/2 e iπ(ν+1/2)/2 H (1) ν (-c h,S kη), (C.7) σ + h (η, k) = +i H √ π 2 (-η) 3/2 e -iπ(ν+1/2)/2 H (2) ν (-c h,S kη), (C.8)and the helical bulk-bulk propagator can be written asG (h) σ (η 1, η 2, k) = σ + h (η 1, k)σ + h (η 2, k) σ - h (η 1, k) σ + h (η 1, k) - σ - h (η 0, k) σ + h (η 0, k) θ(η 1 -η 2)+(η 1 ↔ η 2).",
    "(C.9)Since the new mode functions only differ from the old ones by a phase, the bulk-bulk propagator is unchanged.",
    "Now as shown in [24], the mode functions satisfy the properties: Note that this property holds for both light and heavy fields."
